      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SINABUN (10) made an encouraging return when he led and fought on well for third at this circuit and distance. Draws wide so may need a little luck but he should be improved by the fresh effort and has more upside than many of these. CERISE RAINBOW (5) had to work to find the front at this circuit and distance last start so did well to stick on to place. Had recorded back-to-back wins at Penrith prior. She is up to winning this if things go her way. RED SAPPHIRE (9) draws wide but came from a similar barrier for a resuming second at this circuit and distance and strikes at 50 per cent when second-up so should be improved. SHADES OF MIKI (6) did a good job to win first up and goes well at this shorter distance with two wins and a placing from three attempts so respect.",
